\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \tab This scene is fairly short. Unlike the vast majority of my scenes, I can probably skip this scene without losing much value. But for the first draft of my novel, I decided to leave everything in and allow the trimming and cutting scenes to happen in later drafts. The primary objectives of this scene are as follows.}
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Pacing: A bit of a pacing and set up scene.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Character development:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0  - Maggie's decision to forgo a relatively inexpensive cab ride to save money, and instead walk 10 city blocks to meet Evan at his office, and quite uncomfortable shoes, illustrates just how money conscious she is.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0  - The fact that she's wearing these uncomfortable shoes and an outfit borrowed from Laura, indicates that attending a nice play in the city is not something she does regularly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 - For readers who are interested and familiar with downtown Chicago, they get a feel for where offices are located relative to the train station.}
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
